product_name: LancomeLip Idole Squalane-12 Butterglow Hydrating Lip Balm
summary: SummaryLancôme Lip Idôle Squalane-12 Butterglow Hydrating Lip Balm is a buttery, lightweight, non-sticky lip balm that is supercharged with 12% squalane, providing instant shine, buildable color, and up to 24H hydration.
details: DetailsFeaturesThe lightweight, non-sticky formula improves the look of vertical lip lines and lip smoothness after 7 days*This glossy lip balm is made with 83% skincare ingredients, including shea butter, jojoba oil, & ceramidesThe hydrating lip balm glides smoothly onto lips providing instant shine, and over time, helps improve skin's moisture barrierAvailable in 14 shades designed to complement your skin toneBenefitsHydrating lip balm with up to 24H HydrationLips appear 27% less dry after 7 days*Lips appear 19% smoother after 7 days*Visibly improves the look of vertical lines after 7 days**Based on expert grading after twice daily useItem 2626206How To UseSwipe this hydrating lip balm onto bare lips for instant color and shine.Sheer out with your finger for a more subtle wash of color. For more pigment, apply multiple layers to build color and shine.Pro-Tip: Before applying Lip Idôle Squalane-12 Butterglow, overline or contour lips with Lip Idôle Lip Shaper for a fuller looking pout.IngredientsPolyglyceryl-2 Triisostearate, Squalane, Bis-Behenyl/Isostearyl/Phytosteryl Dimer Dilinoleyl Dimer Dilinoleate, Butyrospermum Parkii Butter / Shea Butter, Cellulose, Dimer Dilinoleyl Dimer Dilinoleate, Polyglyceryl-3 Beeswax, Helianthus Annuus Seed Cera / Sunflower Seed Wax, Hydrogenated Castor Oil Dimer Dilinoleate, Simmondsia Chinensis Butter / Jojoba Butter, Hydrogenated Jojoba Oil, Candelilla Cera / Candelilla Wax / Cire De Candelilla, Rosa Centifolia Extract / Rosa Centifolia Flower Extract, Camelina Sativa Seed Oil, Canola Oil, Mentha Piperita Oil /Peppermint Oil, Ceramide Np, Saccharomyces Ferment Filtrate, Silica, Aluminum Hydroxide, Propylene Glycol, Citric Acid, Tocopherol, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, CI 45380 / Red 21, CI 45410 / Red 28, Lake, CI 77891 / Titanium Dioxide, CI 19140 / Yellow 5 Lake, Limonene, Benzyl Benzoate, Parfum / Fragrance.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Swipe this hydrating lip balm onto bare lips for instant color and shine.Sheer out with your finger for a more subtle wash of color. For more pigment, apply multiple layers to build color and shine.Pro-Tip: Before applying Lip Idôle Squalane-12 Butterglow, overline or contour lips with Lip Idôle Lip Shaper for a fuller looking pout.

reviews.headline: Very similar to YSL candy glaze but not as moisturizing
reviews.comments: Beautiful colors with the perfect amount of opacity. The shade "Roast Me" is a gorgeous neutral brown. Perfect for fall! The packaging is so luxe and not as bulky as YLS or the Maybelline attempted dupe. I do agree that it's overpriced and isn't super moisturizing compared to YSL's version (it's not drying, just feels like more like a waxy occlusive). Personally, I think we're paying for the name and packaging, but the formula itself is worth $15-20 MAX. I splurged because YSL doesn't have a shade comparable to the one I purchased. I suggest putting on your clear moisturizing balm first, then layering this on top like a gloss for the best wear. Also, Revolution Beauty just dropped their own dupe, so maybe try that first since it's 1/3 of the price.

reviews.headline: Hydrating
reviews.comments: This is the best sheer lip balm crossed with a gloss I've used! It's smooth and hydrating. There's nothing sticky about it. The wind can blow and my hair doesn't tick to my lips!

reviews.headline: Not Moisturizing for Dry Lips
reviews.comments:
I really wanted to love this. So much so that I did love it at first. I have very dry lips and am in constant need of hydration on my lips, but I also want some color on occasion. I got this Butterglow lip balm while on sale, and the scent is really great, not too strong; the color I picked was nice on my skin color. The downside comes when my lips begin to dry after the lip balm is applied, only minutes after. 

The balm seems like it sits on top of my lips and emphasizes any dryness, including cracks and peeling skin. I was so disappointed. It's less of a glossy or thick type of balm and more of a thin kind that sits the color on top. 

I decided to return it.

reviews.headline: Feels like nothing
reviews.comments: I would not recommend this product.

reviews.headline: Nice but a bit too sticky/soft
reviews.comments: I got this on sale and I normally like Lancome's lip products. It's not bad, but I don't know if I'd pay full price. Also, the balm part is quite soft—you can't really apply pressure without deforming the tube or getting way too much on your lips—but it still kind of sticks/drags if you're just trying to swipe over.

reviews.headline: Perfect!!
reviews.comments:
I decided to try this butterglow since it was on the lip gloss promotion.  Wow what a find!! This lipgloss is so smooth and feels so good on my lips.  It's lile butter.  The colors are fabulous. I bought the keep it glowy and was so in love with the color and how it feels that i bought another nude now.  
Both colors are great.  I noticed that they mix with my natural color on my lips to make the perfect shade.  I think I might be done with lip stick and just use this line for my lips.
Ladies you have to try these!!!

reviews.headline: This is the only lipstick I will ever use.
reviews.comments: This lipstick is fantastic.  It really moisturizes, even after is has faded.  It can be made lighter or darker.  I like to use it over top of an all-day lipstick.  I prefer the darker colors but the light are pretty, too.

reviews.headline: Perfect Shade; Very Hydrating
reviews.comments: I am not a fan of lipstick because I never like the feeling of it on my lips and I don't like transfer. I usually prefer a non-sticky gloss. This Lancome Lip Idole Squalane product has perfect coverage, a great neutral colour (12 Butterglow) and is very hydrating. I don't mind the feel of it at all. I stumbled upon it when looking for another product that is never in stock in the color I'd like to try. The price-point of this product is more affordable that the other product I was looking for, too.

reviews.headline: Luxe and buttery without feeling sticky
reviews.comments: Lancôme Lip Idole Squalane-12 Butterglow is a 5-star winner. The sleek packaging feels luxe, and the buttery texture glides on smoothly without feeling sticky. It deeply hydrates, leaves lips soft and plump, and has a light, pleasant scent. Though it's a bit of a splurge, the results and comfort make it totally worth it.

reviews.headline: Buying this again!
reviews.comments: I am 67 yers old with fairly dry skin. I don't like tons of color-just a natural berry colored lip. This product checked all of the boxes!

faceoff_positive.comments:
#### Overview
Lancôme's L'Absolu Rouge Lip Idole in Squalane 12 is a luxurious lipstick that combines high-pigment color with the nourishing benefits of squalane. This product promises to deliver long-lasting, vibrant color while keeping lips moisturized and comfortable throughout the day.

#### Packaging and Presentation
The lipstick comes in an elegant black and gold tube with the iconic Lancôme rose logo embossed on the cap. The magnetic closure ensures that the lid stays secure, preventing accidental opening in your bag. The sleek and sophisticated design makes it a chic addition to any makeup collection.

#### Key Ingredients
- **Squalane:** A highly effective moisturizer that helps to keep lips hydrated, smooth, and supple.
- **Pro-Xylane™:** A proprietary Lancôme ingredient that helps to restore and strengthen the lips' natural moisture barrier.
- **Vitamin E:** An antioxidant that helps to protect the lips from environmental damage.

#### Texture and Application
The L'Absolu Rouge Lip Idole has a creamy, buttery texture that glides effortlessly onto the lips. The formula is lightweight and non-sticky, ensuring comfortable wear. The pointed bullet shape allows for precise application, making it easy to define the lip contours without the need for a lip liner.

#### Color and Finish
Squalane 12 is a rich, vibrant shade that delivers intense pigmentation with just one swipe. The finish is satin, providing a subtle sheen that enhances the lips' natural beauty without looking overly glossy. The color payoff is impressive, with the shade staying true to its appearance in the tube.

#### Hydration and Longevity
Thanks to the inclusion of squalane and other moisturizing ingredients, this lipstick keeps the lips hydrated for hours. It doesn't settle into fine lines or accentuate dry patches, making it ideal for those with dry or sensitive lips. The longevity is commendable, with the color staying vibrant for up to 6-8 hours without the need for frequent touch-ups. Even after eating and drinking, the lipstick fades gracefully, leaving a subtle stain behind.

#### Benefits
- **Moisturizing:** Keeps lips hydrated and comfortable throughout the day.
- **Pigmentation:** Delivers rich, vibrant color with a single application.
- **Comfort:** Lightweight and non-sticky formula ensures all-day comfort.
- **Luxurious Packaging:** Elegant design with a secure magnetic closure.
- **Versatility:** Suitable for both everyday wear and special occasions.

#### Suitability
- **All Skin Types:** The moisturizing formula is suitable for all skin types, including sensitive and dry lips.
- **All Occasions:** The versatile shade and finish make it perfect for both daytime and evening looks.

#### Pros
- Rich, vibrant color with a satin finish.
- Long-lasting wear with minimal touch-ups.
- Hydrating formula that keeps lips smooth and supple.
- Elegant, secure packaging.
- Easy, precise application.

#### Cons
- Premium price point may not be accessible for all budgets.
- Limited shade availability may not suit all skin tones.

#### Conclusion
Lancôme's L'Absolu Rouge Lip Idole in Squalane 12 is a standout product for anyone seeking a high-quality, moisturizing lipstick with vibrant color payoff. Its luxurious formula and elegant packaging make it a worthwhile investment for both everyday use and special occasions. While it comes at a premium price, the benefits of hydration, comfort, and long-lasting wear make it a must-have for lipstick lovers.
faceoff_positive.headline: Will buy it again

faceoff_negative.comments: The packaging is beautiful but dont be suckered into buying this product, i bought this October 29th and received it in the mail October 31st. I didnt start using the product until November 1st, the first time I applied it I wasnt sure how I felt it was smooth but I could feel the dryness of my lips so I exfoliated that night and throughout the weekend I tried it again and it still felt a little gritty even though my lips were not chapped. I found myself reapplying this product multiple times throughout the day because it leaves a thick residue on things you drink out of. I found that by the end of the day my lips would have a strange feeling to them and they would be dry and chapped. I have only had this for a couple of weeks and I already ran out, I do feel like this product is overpriced for the quality and the fact you run out of it so fast because of how often you need to reapply. I would recommend saving your money and trying a different product even though I really love this brand.
faceoff_negative.headline: It's a no for me

variant_names: Hydrating Lip Balm with Instant Color & Shine
